  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt at restitution by paying back a portion of the stolen funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate for this amount of money and personal background. The outburst from the spectator is legally irrelevant and was disregarded for sentencing purposes. Balancing the need for accountability with the potential for rehabilitation, a sentence of 6 months is appropriate to reflect the seriousness of the offense without being overly punitive.",
  "verdict": 6
}
